Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ae̯ˈkʷi.wo.koː/, [ae̯ˈkᶣɪ.wɔ.koː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /eˈkwi.vo.ko/, [ɛˈkwiː.vɔ.kɔ]

Etymology 1[edit]

Derived from aequus (“equal”) +‎ -i- (connecting vowel) +‎ vocō (“I call”).

Verb[edit]

aequivocō (present infinitive aequivocāre, perfect active aequivocāvī, supine aequivocātum); first conjugation

  1. (Late Latin) I call or name in the same way.
